title: 17-year-old motorcyclist killed in Waukegan crash identified
text:
A 17-year-old motorcyclist who was killed in a three-vehicle crash Saturday afternoon in north suburban Waukegan has been identified.
The crash, involving the motorcycle and two other vehicles, happened on Jackson Street between Washington Street and Glen Rock Avenue, according to Waukegan police.
The motorcyclist, identified as 17-year-old Anthony Young of Zion, was killed in the crash, police said.
No other serious injuries were reported, police said.
